The **Breusch-Godfrey test** is specifically designed to detect autocorrelation up to a specified lag order (including third-order), making it the appropriate choice here. The **Durbin-Watson test (E)** is limited to first-order autocorrelation, while other options (e.g., Dickey-Fuller, Phillips-Perron) focus on unit root testing.
